<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUL 92 / Growth hope for Australia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN BROWN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
THE Australian economy is likely to grow about 4 per cent in the year to
June 1993, after growing about 2 per cent in 1991-92, Mr Paul Keating, the
prime minister, said yesterday.
Forecasts suggest Australia's real GDP grew about 0.6 per cent in the fourth
quarter of 1991/92, after growth of 1.4 per cent in the first three
quarters. The government seems to have abandoned hope that growth would
reach 4.75 per cent in the current year. The weakness of the recovery is
reflected in the unemployment level, up from 10.5 per cent in February to
11.1 per cent.
</TEXT>
