</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BUCHAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Unemployment in the European Community will rise from an average 9.5 per
cent this year to 9.7 per cent next year, the Commission forecast in its
annual employment report yesterday, writes David Buchan in Brussels.
Ms Vasso Papandreou, the EC employment commissioner, warned that the targets
for economic convergence and fiscal austerity, set down in the Maastricht
treaty, 'should not be achieved at the expense of unemployment which is
already too high'.
