<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
PEPSICO, the US soft drinks, snacks and fast-food restaurant group,
yesterday unveiled a 20 per cent improvement in second-quarter net profits,
with strong gains in overseas markets.
Net income for the three months to June 13 totalled Dollars 383m, or 48
cents a share, compared with Dollars 318.3m, or 39 cents, in the same period
last year. Sales advanced 11 per cent to Dollars 5.21bn.
Mr Wayne Calloway, chief executive, said earnings momentum had been based on
