achieving double-digit growth in both their US and international
operations'.
PepsiCo saw a 9 per cent increase in soft drink sales to Dollars 3.42bn,
with international sales for the division surging 18 per cent to Dollars
926.9m. Operating profits for the division rose 8 per cent to Dollars
452.2m.
PepsiCo's snack foods operations had operating profits of Dollars 459.1m, up
20 per cent, on sales which rose 8 per cent to Dollars 2.74bn. The
improvement was driven by strong gains overseas, where operating profits
soared 39 per cent to Dollars 125.5m.
For the first half, PepsiCo posted a 19 per cent gain in net income to
Dollars 624.5m, or 78 cents a share, on sales which rose 11 per cent to
Dollars 9.8bn.
