FT  22 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Reuters plans global TV expansion
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Reuters said yesterday that its 10-year television partnership with NBC
would allow it to explore new opportunities in global television with its US
partner, writes Andrew Bolger.
It will buy out minority stakes in Visnews, the international television
news agency, held by NBC and the BBC and eventually aims to put together its
conventional news agency operation with Visnews to form the world's largest
reporting network.
Visnews will continue to produce mainly raw news feeds to existing
programmes and networks, although it already produces some complete
programmes of its own.
It has 454 staff worldwide while Reuters has 1,100 reporters and
photographers.
