FT  22 JUL 92 / UK Company News: Central Motor halved
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CAPITAL SPENDING on site development contributed to a halving of pre-tax
profits at Central Motor Auctions.
Auction proceeds, excluding VAT, for this USM-quoted company, fell Pounds 3m
to Pounds 152.8m for profits of Pounds 432,000 (Pounds 861,000).
The result was struck after a downturn from interest received of Pounds
156,000 to Pounds 112,000 payable as a result of the capital expenditure,
and included exceptionals of Pounds 165,000 (Pounds 256,000) from property
sales.
Earnings per share came out at 2.7p (5.1p). The interim dividend is
maintained at 1p.
