FT  22 JUL 92 / Publishers told to play by the book
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Terry Maher, chairman of Pentos, which runs the Dillons bookshop chain,
has written to UK publishers urging them to drop support for the net book
agreement. He argued that a recent judgment from European Court of First
Instance rendered the agreement 'unlawful' in the UK and that the chances of
modifying it to reflect the court's concerns about its restrictive
implications were 'remote'.
'In our view the PA (the Publishers' Association) and its members should no
longer expend further time and substantial amounts of your money to salvage
arrangements which are anti-competitive, anachronistic and incompatible with
Community law,' he wrote.
The Publishers' Association has argued that the court's ruling is narrow and
solely applies to interstate trade.
