<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUL 92 / Naval vessel flees Crimean port
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A Black Sea Fleet vessel yesterday fled its naval base of Donuzlav in Crimea
for the Ukrainian port of Odessa, agencies report.
A navy spokesman for the Commonwealth of Independent States said several
vessels gave chase to the unnamed coastguard vessel, which raised the
Ukrainian flag and defied demands by Russian naval commanders to return.
