<HEADLINE>
FT  22 JUL 92 / UK Company News: St Modwen bucks trend with rise to Pounds
1.04m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT, Midlands Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ST MODWEN Properties, the Birmingham-based investment and development
company, yesterday defied the general sector trend by announcing a marginal
increase in interim profits.
For the six months to May 31 profits rose from Pounds 1.02m to Pounds 1.04m
at the pre-tax level. Turnover was Pounds 11.4m, against Pounds 33.4m last
time when sales were inflated by one unusually large property sale. Earnings
per share were unchanged at 0.6p.
The company is now receiving rental income in excess of interest payments
and, according to Mr Stan Clarke, chairman, by the end of this financial
year rental income will cover both interest charges and management costs.
Gross rental income during the first half was Pounds 3.3m, but interest
charges were Pounds 2.5m (Pounds 3.2m). The company does not capitalise its
interest charges. Gearing was fractionally reduced to 85 per cent but is
expected to show a modest rise by the year-end.
Mr Clarke, through a personal company, is injecting Pounds 1.56m into
Uttoxeter Leisure &amp; Development, 81 per cent controlled by St Modwen and
owner of the Uttoxeter racecourse. The injection, in exchange for shares,
will have the effect of eliminating the racecourse company's debts to St
Modwen and provide funds for course improvement.
</TEXT>
