<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 92 / Wellcome price likely to be 800p
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MAGGIE URRY and ALAN FRIEDMAN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON, NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A PRICE of at least 800p looks likely to be set for the sale of 330m shares
in Wellcome, the pharmaceutical group, after Robert Fleming, the merchant
bank organising the sale, said last night it had received indicative bids
for more than 250m shares at prices between 800p and 850p.
The tender offer of shares, through which Wellcome Trust, the medical
charity, will reduce its stake from 73.5 per cent to 35 per cent, closes on
Friday.
Fleming said it would make no further announcement about the level of
demand. Wellcome's shares fell 25p to 845p yesterday, and an 800p strike
price would represent a 5 per cent discount. Bankers involved in the deal
said that some progress was made in the book-building process yesterday in
spite of the weakness of the UK stock market and Wellcome's shares.
Indicative bids for about three-quarters of the stock have been made. The
poor stock market background is putting pressure on the sale, but the level
of bids indicated should ensure that the offer is not cancelled. The trust
can reduce the number of shares it sells if it is not satisfied with the
price.
The falling market yesterday meant that some investors cancelled bids put in
earlier, but others made new ones. Bids are indicative until Friday. Many
investors are putting in prices of 800p knowing that they can be increased
later if demand seems to improve.
In the US, which is expected to account for about a quarter of the shares on
offer, institutional investors were yesterday advised to tender for Wellcome
shares at a price of 800p. The recommendation came from Mehta and Isaly, the
New York analysts. However Mr Sam Isaly said: 'This is not a strong
recommendation. This is a tolerance at 800p.' He said the plan to sell 80m
shares to US investors could be achieved, but was difficult to sell to some
institutions.
Some US institutional investors said they liked Wellcome as a company, but
would require a reasonable discount to the group's share price if they were
to participate. Several investors, who have seen the company's roadshow, say
they would be interested in Wellcome shares at prices between 750p and 800p.
The UK public offer closes today. By yesterday's close, bids for more than
Pounds 100m worth of stock had been made, less than the Pounds 180m set
aside for retail investors.
Market, Page 34
