<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 92 / Observer: Broke away
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Is the writing now officially on the wall for the profession of broker's
analyst? The Society of Investment Analysts, after 37 years, has changed its
name to the Institute of Investment Management and Research - a clear sign
that it thinks its future lies with investment managers on the 'buy' side of
the investment world, rather than with the brokers on the 'sell' side.
The shift of emphasis has been under consideration for a decade, says the
institute's current president Chris Davis, himself an analyst at BZW.
Although the 2,000-strong membership is split equally, a look at student
enrolments finally made up the new institute's mind. Seven of every 10 of
them are employed by investment managers, while only 30 per cent work for
brokers.
</TEXT>
