<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 92 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
There was good demand with 12,726 packages for the day reports the Tea
Brokers' Association. Landed brightest liquoring East Africans remained
about steady. Better mediums sold at fully firm rates and lesser
descriptions were often dearer. Price levels for Central African teas showed
little change. Offshore good demand for the brighter cif offerings at fully
firm to dearer rates: plainer sorts tended lower where sold. Fob teas from
Mauritius sold at last levels. The highest price realised this week was 200p
for rwanda pf. 1. Quotations: quality 165p, nom good medium 135p, medium
112p, low medium 83p.
</TEXT>
