fell sharply - from Pounds 724,000 to Pounds 188,000 - reflecting the
depressed property market. Nevertheless, the 75 per cent owned Bridger
Properties offshoot reduced its pre-tax loss to Pounds 289,000 (Pounds
417,000).
After a reduced tax charge, earnings per share edged ahead to 11.89p
(10.97p). A recommended final dividend of 3.75p maintains the total at
6.75p.
