<TEXT>
Britain's hard-pressed construction industry cont-inues to ring the
management changes. The latest move involves John Stanion who becomes chief
executive of Norwest Holst, a wholly owned subsidiary of Societe Generale
d'Entreprises, the large French construction group.
Stanion, 40, was formerly managing director of Beazer Kier which formed a
big part of the contracting division of Beazer Group which was acquired last
year by Hanson.
Beazer's contracting arm, without Stanion, was sold to its employees and
