FT  21 JUL 92 / World Trade News: Textiles group attacks Pakistan
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID DODWELL, World Trade Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
EUROPE'S largest textiles and apparel companies have called for a 'test
case' investigation into alleged Pakistani abuses in a swingeing attack on
misuse of export subsidies among five leading third world textiles
exporters.
Europe's Largest Textile and Apparel Companies (Eltac), an umbrella grouping
for the European industry, is also asking for a joint committee on subsidies
to be set up with the European Commission.
Eltac complains that the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade and the
European Commission - the two main watchdogs for abuse of subsidies - are
'largely ineffective'.
In a study of government support for textile exporters in Pakistan, India,
Indonesia, China and Turkey, Eltac says Pakistan is 'clearly the worst
offender'. It endorses the view of the Asian Development Bank that the
Pakistan government's policy of providing cut-price raw cotton to textile
manufacturers 'has reached such proportions as to be branded an economic
nonsense'.
