<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JUL 92 / French industrial production falls 1.6 per cent
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
French industrial production fell by 1.6 per cent in May, a sharp turnround
from the 1.5 per cent increase in April, said Insee, the state statistics
body. It attributed the fall to a 5.5 per cent decline in energy
consumption, due to warm weather in May.
Manufacturing industry production was roughly stable over the period, a more
accurate indication of the real trend.
</TEXT>
